<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="121" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Audit wizard file summary — reproduce failure, categorize, recommend restoration vs remediation</title>
    <phase>Wave 12 — MVP Completion</phase>
    <wave>12</wave>
    <sub-wave>12.1</sub-wave>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Read-only audit; no code modification; output is a notes doc</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>W12-1-Audit</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <tags>audit, bff-api, wizard, playbook, investigation, wave12</tags>
    <estimated-effort>~half day</estimated-effort>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
The wizard-based file summary feature is currently broken but was previously working. Audit it: locate the code, reproduce the failure, categorize the root cause (R7 regression vs inherent playbook engine bug class), and recommend restoration vs remediation with effort estimates per path.
  </prompt>

  <role>
You are a code auditor doing read-only investigation. Do NOT modify code. Do NOT run deployments. Your job is to produce a concrete audit that enables Wave 12.3 task generation with a disposition (restore vs remediate) and realistic effort estimate.
  </role>

  <goal>
Output a notes doc at projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/audits/wave12-121-wizard-file-summary.md containing: (1) location of all code involved (BFF endpoint + playbook definition + UI invocation), (2) reproduced failure with diagnostic detail, (3) root-cause categorization, (4) disposition recommendation (restore or remediate) with effort estimate.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    - Operator-reported state: feature was previously working; currently broken
    - Likely architecture: simple Start → AiCompletion → ReturnResponse playbook + BFF endpoint + wizard UI in code page
    - R7 brought enum rename (ActionType → ExecutorType, ~1000+ references), DI changes, dispatch refactor — any could have regressed simple playbooks
    - Engine bug classes from R7 W11 T116 systematic assessment: aggregator IsDeliverOutput drops ReturnResponse, LoadKnowledge type mismatch, template substitution edges, fan-out 0-iterations, ValidateEntityNames allow-list mismatches
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    - Read-only. No code edits. No deploys. No Dataverse writes.
    - Investigate only — do NOT propose code fixes inside this task. Wave 12.3 POMLs handle that.
    - Cite file:line references for every claim.
    - If failure is reproducible without deploys, that's preferred evidence.
    - Sub-Agent Write Boundary: writes go ONLY to projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/audits/.
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/wave12-mvp-completion-plan.md (§2.2 Wizards scope)
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/handoffs/wave11-t116-narrate-systematic-assessment.md (engine bug class documentation)
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/poc-vs-playbook-engine-architecture.md
      - .claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <relevant-files>
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/** (BFF endpoint — search for "file-summary" / "summary" / "summarize")
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookOrchestrationService.cs
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/InvokePlaybookAi.cs (aggregator with known bug class)
      - src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/** (potential wizard UI location)
      - src/client/code-pages/** (alternate wizard UI location)
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <steps>
1. **Locate feature code** (30 min):
   - Search BFF endpoints for "file-summary" / "summary" / similar
   - Search code pages / SpaarkeAi for wizard UI invocation
   - Identify playbook (sprk_analysisplaybook row) — search consumer-type or code matching "file-summary"
   - Document: BFF endpoint file:line, UI entry point file:line, playbook ID + node count

2. **Inspect playbook shape** (20 min):
   - Use mcp__dataverse__describe / mcp__dataverse__read_query on relevant tables
   - Query deployed playbook + nodes
   - Document: node count, executor types used, fan-out / iteration / complex composition presence
   - Categorize: SIMPLE (Start → AiCompletion → ReturnResponse) or COMPLEX (multi-node, fan-out, validators)

3. **Trace data flow end-to-end** (45 min):
   - Walk: UI → BFF endpoint → IInvokePlaybookAi → orchestrator → executors → response
   - At each step: what changed in R7 (enum rename, dispatch, DI)
   - At each step: which engine bug classes (aggregator, LoadKnowledge, templates) apply

4. **Reproduce failure if possible** (30-45 min):
   - If deployed environment accessible: invoke wizard, capture network/console errors
   - If not: walk through expected vs actual at each step
   - If reproducible in tests: run `dotnet test` filtered to relevant tests
   - Document: failure symptom + evidence + which step is the actual break

5. **Categorize root cause** (20 min):
   - **R7 regression**: enum rename / DI change / dispatch refactor broke reference → cheap restoration (1-2 hours)
   - **Inherent engine bug class**: matches /narrate modes → remediation needed (3-5 days)
   - **Configuration drift**: Dataverse row data wrong (wiped configJson, missing FK) → restoration via data fix
   - **Missing implementation**: never fully shipped → out of restoration scope; remediation = greenfield

6. **Produce disposition recommendation** (20 min):
   - If R7 regression: name exact regression + fix (e.g., "line X references ActionType, should be ExecutorType")
   - If engine bug class: cite which class + recommend thin code-defined wrapper (~50-100 LOC) preserving Action output schema
   - Effort estimate per disposition

7. **Write notes doc** at projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/audits/wave12-121-wizard-file-summary.md (30 min)

  </steps>

  <tools>
    - Read (file inspection)
    - Grep / Glob (code search)
    - Bash (dotnet test if useful; curl smoke)
    - mcp__dataverse__describe / mcp__dataverse__read_query (playbook row inspection)
    - Write (notes doc only)
    - TodoWrite (track audit progress)
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    - notes/audits/wave12-121-wizard-file-summary.md
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    - [ ] BFF endpoint + UI entry point + playbook ID located with file:line references
    - [ ] Playbook shape documented (SIMPLE vs COMPLEX) with node count + executor types
    - [ ] Failure reproduced OR walked through with predicted-failure-point identified
    - [ ] Root cause categorized (R7 regression / engine bug class / config drift / missing impl)
    - [ ] Disposition recommended (restore vs remediate) with effort estimate
    - [ ] notes/audits/wave12-121-wizard-file-summary.md exists with file:line references throughout
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
